gov.usgs.anss.ewexport

Class TraceBufQueue

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.ewexport.TraceBufQueue

  • public class TraceBufQueue
extends java.lang.Object
    This class was written as a queue between a EWExportSocket and and EWExportOutputer. It contains a fixed size set of TraceBufs. TraceBufs are preallocated on the queue and "queuing" consists of copying the tracebufs to one of the internal elements. in this way the queuer is free to reuse the input tracebuf. The dequeue is a two step process 1) the actual object on the queue is returned with getTail(), when processing of this has been completed, the user calls bumpTail() to indicate the space can now be reused. All of this was done to make it so TraceBufs would not be created and destroyed all of the time, but reused in place.
